Initial reports received by the National Sea Rescue Institute s Wilderness duty crew at about 4.48pm said that five people had been carried out. Our sea rescue craft Oscars Rescuer Clemengold rescuer and Die Swart Tobie out on the water at the time conducting routine training diverted to the scene and on our arrival we found that four men aged in their late 20s from The Netherlands had been swept out to sea by rip-currents said duty controller Saria van As.She said the lifeguards had managed to rescue three of the men safely from about 200m and one lifeguard remained with the fourth man 400m off-shore assisting the man to stay afloat and they were taken aboard our sea rescue craft and brought safely ashore . No one was injured Van As said. TMG Digital